cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the impact of batch normalization on the training of deep neural networks and its effect on adversarial vulnerability. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since the paper evaluates the performance on image datasets, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of batch normalization on the robustness of the model, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the relationship between batch normalization and exploding gradients, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
